      {
        "id": 4023399,
        "name": "Chris Seiber",
        "username": "Chris_Seiber",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/chris_seiber/{size}/1144_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-03-06T02:40:04.829Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I pulled this at random without realizing what a terrific wine experience I was about to have.  So it\u2019s fun to be pleasantly surprised.  I now look back and see that <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/william_kelley\">@William_Kelley</a> and others have talked this producer up a lot.</p>\n<p>On to the wine, this is delicious right out of the gate at cellar temperature.  Pale gold and straw color, lovely saline and tart pineapple nose.  This doesn\u2019t have \u201clook at how impressive I am\u201d concentration and power, but it has terrific balance of all things: fruit, savory notes, complexity, clarity, precision.  White nectarine, sweet lemon, gentle white spices, and an elegant finish laced with river rock mineral and sea breeze.</p>\n<p>Excellent QPR at around $50.  I\u2019m buying the hype here.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
