        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Monopole_Cru\" data-username=\"Chris_Seiber\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"298273\" data-full=\"true\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/chris_seiber/48/1144_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Chris_Seiber:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The only reason I got to try it was because folks like <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/william_kelley\">@William_Kelley</a> and <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/jeremy_holmes\">@Jeremy_Holmes</a> shared what they knew.</p>\n<p>I\u2019m sure the prices for this wine will rise a lot if they keep making this quality. Hopefully fellow WBers tell me about the next young buck making great chardonnay from satellite Burg appellations at that time.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Sorry Chris, you are right, that was a dumb response.<br>\nKeep searching these wines. They are fabulous\u2026I will pop one soon and post a note too.</p>",
